				 Luxury wines bubble over
 KAKOLY CHATTERJEE				 	 FINE TASTES																								New Delhi, Oct. 14: Luxury wine distributor Finewinesmore has a rich bouquet in offer for Indian connoisseurs. The company plans to launch exclusive labels from all over the world for the upwardly mobile citizen who prefers an aromatic wine to a stiff whisky.																								We will add Californian and South African wines to our portfolio very soon and the number of labels will rise to 150, said Sumedh Singh Mandla, partner, Finewinesmore. 																								Finewinesmore recently launched 35 brands and 115 labels from France, Italy, Spain, Germany, Australia, New Zealand, Chile and Mexico.																								The company is present in Mumbai, Delhi, Gurgaon, Faridabad, Pune, Goa, Rajasthan, Bangalore and Chennai. Mandla said the distributor planned to start operating in Calcutta in a month. It will sell the products through top-notch hotels.																								Dharti Desai, Mandlas partner in Finewinesmore, said, We are planning to start with wines, but will soon add other beverages such as martinique rum, grappas, limoncello, tequila and vodka.																								We have tied up with Marriott, Meridien, Park and Hyatt to sell wines through institutions, she added.																								Finewinesmore also plans to import water, which it will supply to the hotels.																								After expanding our beverage portfolio, we will distribute Mediterranean fruits such as olive and other culinary items such as olive oil and pasta, Desai said.																								The company also aims to ride the crest of the Indian retail boom. 
